The Nigeria Aviation Handling Company, NAHCO Aviance, Plc has acquired and installed state-of-the-art set of equipment for effective service delivery in the industry. Group Managing Director, NAHCOAviance, Mrs. Olatokunbo Fagbemi, explained that the feat, which is part of the companyâ€™s five years transformational plan, was to further position the brand as one of the leading aviation handling firms in Africa. A statement quoted Fagbemi, to have stated this at a pre-annual general meeting forum in Kano on Thursday. She said the aviation handling company is set to use the development to sustain its high level of service delivery across both domestic and international airports in Nigeria and indirectly boost its revenue. Speaking on the development, the Chief Operating Officer, NAHCO Aviance, Mr. Herbert Odika, lauded the effort of the new management of the company as he is optimistic that the new set of equipment would aid service delivery and help staff turnaround aircraft within the record time across domestic and the international airports in Nigeria. Why NAHCO adopted group structure - GMD NAHCO targets N13.3bn turnover in 2019 NAHCO Plc names Fagbemi new GMD/CEO Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin